<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!-- Do not remove this test for UTF-8: if “Ω” doesn’t appear as greek uppercase omega letter enclosed in quotation marks, you should use an editor that supports UTF-8, not this one. -->
<package xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/packaging/2015/06/nuspec.xsd">
  <metadata>
    <id>bitbucket-cli</id>
    <version>0.18.0</version>
    <owners>Gildas Cherruel</owners>
    <title>bitbucket-cli (Install)</title>
    <authors>Gildas Cherruel</authors>
    <projectUrl>https://github.com/gildas/bitbucket-cli</projectUrl>
    <packageSourceUrl>https://github.com/gildas/bitbucket-cli/blob/master/packaging/chocolatey</packageSourceUrl>
    <licenseUrl>https://github.com/gildas/bitbucket-cli/blob/master/LICENSE</licenseUrl>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <projectSourceUrl>https://github.com/gildas/bitbucket-cli/blob/master</projectSourceUrl>
    <docsUrl>https://github.com/gildas/bitbucket-cli/blob/master/README.md</docsUrl>
    <bugTrackerUrl>https://github.com/gildas/bitbucket-cli/issues</bugTrackerUrl>
    <tags>bitbucket cli</tags>
    <summary>Command line interface for Bitbucket</summary>
    <description>The Bitbucket Command Line Interface brings the power of the Bitbucket platform to your command line. Creating and merging Pull Requests, cloning repositories, and more are now just a few keystrokes away.</description>
    <releaseNotes>
- Most commands now support --workspace and --repository flags to specify the target workspace and repository. By default, they are inferred from the current git repository and the profile.
- Pull request subcommands infer their pull request ID like merge does
- New pull request subcommand: bb pullrequest activities to replace bb pullrequest activity list (marked as deprecated)
- New pull request subcommands: commits, diff, patch, request-changes, task
- Pull request merge can now be performed with the --async flag to avoid waiting for the merge to complete
- Pull requests can now be searched by a commit ID with bb pullrequest list --commit commit-id
- Bug fixes
    </releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
  <files>
    <file src="tools\**" target="tools" />
  </files>
</package>
